    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "hasOperatingEnvelope": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/envelope",
      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "ASTM F1717 compression-bending operating envelope for 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw",
      "description": "Axial compressive load range: 0–2500 N. Bending moment arm: 40 mm fixed offset per ASTM F1717 fixture. Crosshead displacement rate: 5 mm/min ± 0.5 mm/min. Screw outer diameter: 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm. Screw length: 45–55 mm. UHMWPE block density: 0.94–0.96 g/cm³. Test temperature: 23 ± 2 °C. Rod diameter: 5.5 mm Ti-6Al-4V. Construct span: 44 mm. All simulations use linear elastic Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E = 114 GPa, ν = 0.34)."
    },
    "hasApplicabilityConstraint": {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated/applicability",
      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "Applicability domain: non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under static compression-bending",
      "description": "Results apply exclusively to non-cannulated pedicle screws with outer diameter 7.5 mm ± 0.1 mm, tested under static (quasi-static) ASTM F1717 compression-bending loading. Excludes cannulated variants, dynamic fatigue loading, screws with outer diameter outside 7.3–7.6 mm range, and constructs assembled with rods other than 5.5 mm Ti-6Al-4V. Spinal levels T10–L5 only; cervical and sacral constructs are out of scope."
    }
  },
